<br>
Flash of light is awesome taunt, until the mob runs for whatever reason.  Then your in trouble with your group.  Unless you can be sure of not getting adds it's not worth it.<br>
<br>
<br>
stun,cease,desist are great when you want agro and dont' want to risk breaking a mez.  This is my chanter bodygaurd setup.<br>
<br>
stun,cease,holy might are used when dmg doesn't matter and I still want fast casting.  Usually when I main tank in exp group.<br>
<br>
stun,force,wot are used for interupting giants or other non stunnable classes.  The knockback isn't guaranteed to interupt but it does have the best chance of all the stuff we have.  You can move a giant a long way when you use these back to back.<br>
<br>
<br>
Taunt is a given for this and the procs are also helpful in keeping agro.  The main thing though is stun.  That one spell gives you all the agro you will ever want to have if you use it right.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, one thing no one else mentioned.  Sitting down.  Drop 3 stuns on something, move to where you want the mob to go and sit down.  If you used non damaging stuns the mob won't summon you , but will move thru a pack of 50 people to get you.  It doesn't always work, but I've found it's helpful when something needs moved and you can't dammage it. <p>Chavr Wyrmbane<br>
